This paper is likely to belong to the Computer Vision (cs.CV) category as it deals with image generation and disentangling of attributes in video sequences. It also involves the use of Generative Adversarial Networks (GANs) which is a popular technique in computer vision. The paper also involves machine learning techniques such as unsupervised learning and adversarial training, which are commonly used in the categories of Machine Learning (cs.LG) and Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI). Additionally, the paper involves the use of video datasets, which could also place it in the categories of Multimedia (cs.MM) and Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE).
